2026-05-18	tuneup.exe aborts with CPU exception on ARM64 if
		**NOT** compiled with assembly. Visual C/C++ seems
		to violate ARM64 ABI by modifying register X23...

2026-05-16	not a bug here but in armasm64.exe: 'ALIGN 16'
		directive in CODE sections emits 0x00000000 opcodes
		instead of NOP aka 'HINT #0x0' aka opcode 0xD503201F.
		On ARM64/Aarch64, this is AN INVALID OPCODE and
		crashes the assembler stuff.

		Actually: all 'ALIGN 16' without 'ret' or 'b'(ranch)
		--------- were manually replaced by one or more of
		          the correct opcode 0xD503201F.

2026-05-15	tuneup.exe exits creating MULFFT stuff; possibly
		'long' C type (32bit in 64bit compiler) problem



